1
00:01:26,355 --> 00:01:29,952
<i>[Begin Again]</i>

2
00:01:41,879 --> 00:01:42,976
Come in.

3
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:47,040
Ms. Tang, why are you looking for me
in the dead of night?

4
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:51,719
Miss Xu Jiajia, you aren't getting
married until tomorrow.

5
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:54,319
And I can't look for you now?

6
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:55,959
You're unpredictable.

7
00:01:55,959 --> 00:01:57,480
What if you suddenly change your mind

8
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,760
and take me back to Shanghai?

9
00:02:01,359 --> 00:02:02,464
If you keep this up, I'm leaving.

10
00:02:03,359 --> 00:02:04,640
Don't disturb anyone, come in quickly.

11
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:06,959
I want to have a quick chat with you.

12
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:10,120
Being so reluctant.

13
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,168
Ouch.

14
00:02:12,723 --> 00:02:15,840
<i>[Episode 17]</i>

15
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,024
What is this?

16
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:19,808
Open it.

17
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,879
Although you advocate for a simple wedding,

18
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:30,159
I think this tradition of combing the hair

19
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,280
is something I don't want to let go of.

20
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:47,319
Did you also have this ceremony
when you married Dad?

21
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:51,712
Of course.

22
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:58,759
So did Grandma comb your hair?

23
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:09,800
Speaking of which, it's really a shame

24
00:03:12,199 --> 00:03:13,599
that your grandma

25
00:03:13,599 --> 00:03:16,479
didn't get to see you in your bridal attire.

26
00:03:17,039 --> 00:03:21,360
Otherwise, she'd definitely be grinning

27
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:24,719
with her toothless mouth.

28
00:03:31,919 --> 00:03:33,000
But it's fine.

29
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,919
She can see it all from heaven.

30
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:41,800
Right, she can see it from above.

31
00:03:45,919 --> 00:03:47,360
Enough talk, or we'll miss the auspicious time.

32
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,448
Come on, put down your bag.

33
00:04:01,439 --> 00:04:07,360
First brush to the end.

34
00:04:12,159 --> 00:04:19,800
Second brush to the brows white as snow.

35
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:30,079
Third brush for children
and grandchildren all around.

36
00:04:42,279 --> 00:04:46,639
In the blink of an eye,
my daughter has grown so much.

37
00:04:46,639 --> 00:04:49,079
My daughter is getting married tomorrow.

38
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,319
Why suddenly so sentimental?

39
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:07,600
I thought about it carefully.

40
00:05:08,879 --> 00:05:11,959
The last time I combed your hair,

41
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:15,639
you were probably only
seven or eight years old.

42
00:05:15,639 --> 00:05:17,160
Every day, you asked me

43
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,920
to tie your hair full of little braids.

44
00:05:20,759 --> 00:05:22,079
Because it's pretty.

45
00:05:22,079 --> 00:05:23,104
Yeah.

46
00:05:27,439 --> 00:05:29,439
It doesn't seem like a few years have passed,

47
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:32,360
but how have you grown so big?

48
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,192
Mom.

49
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,680
No matter how much I grow,
I'll always be your daughter.

50
00:05:44,519 --> 00:05:45,879
Nothing will change.

51
00:05:58,160 --> 00:05:59,879
Two crybabies.

52
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:06,560
Who's that? Bad timing.

53
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,959
Come on, wipe your face.

54
00:06:07,959 --> 00:06:09,024
So ugly.

55
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,128
Who is it?

56
00:06:15,328 --> 00:06:16,439
- Come on.
- Ms. Wei.

57
00:06:16,439 --> 00:06:17,560
Come on in.

58
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,959
I brought a gift for Jiajia.

59
00:06:20,759 --> 00:06:21,800
Could you give it to her for me?

60
00:06:22,839 --> 00:06:24,120
If you've brought a gift for Jiajia,

61
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,959
you should give it to her in person.

62
00:06:25,959 --> 00:06:27,600
- She's inside.
- Oh, she's in your room.

63
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,959
- Jiajia.
- Jiajia.

64
00:06:28,959 --> 00:06:31,639
I heard there's a gift. Is it for me?

65
00:06:31,639 --> 00:06:32,839
- Of course.
- Of course, it's for you.

66
00:06:32,839 --> 00:06:35,040
You are the most important person today.

67
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,439
- Thank you.
- Go ahead and open it.

68
00:06:48,279 --> 00:06:52,360
I mean you should treat Li Meng nicely.

69
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,519
Whether a woman is happy or not,

70
00:06:53,519 --> 00:06:55,560
you can tell by her smile.

71
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,839
But she smiles every day.

72
00:06:56,839 --> 00:06:58,360
That's because she's pleasing you.

73
00:07:19,079 --> 00:07:20,480
Another cup of pure drink, please.

74
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:21,568
Alright, sir.

75
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,112
Okay, thank you.

76
00:07:37,639 --> 00:07:39,439
Professor Xu, what a coincidence.

77
00:07:42,464 --> 00:07:43,519
Do you still remember me?

78
00:07:43,519 --> 00:07:44,608
Chen.

79
00:07:45,279 --> 00:07:46,368
Hello, hello.

80
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,079
Hello, could I have the same drink, please?

81
00:07:49,079 --> 00:07:50,079
Sure.

82
00:07:50,079 --> 00:07:51,136
Thank you.

83
00:07:54,639 --> 00:07:55,648
Cheers.

84
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:04,544
Thanks.

85
00:08:16,639 --> 00:08:20,079
Professor Xu, I wonder if it's convenient
for me to take up some of your time.

86
00:08:21,696 --> 00:08:22,800
Go ahead.

87
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:25,240
I've heard that the variety show 'Game Theory'

88
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:27,240
has invited you to be a guest.

89
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,639
And you seem to have declined them.

90
00:08:31,759 --> 00:08:34,639
Chen, what does this have to do with your job?

91
00:08:35,879 --> 00:08:37,159
Well, to be frank with you,

92
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,440
Ms. Wei has invested in Tianqin Entertainment.

93
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:44,320
Their annual report is related to me.

94
00:08:49,639 --> 00:08:51,712
So this is what she meant
when she said "our future".

95
00:08:52,256 --> 00:08:53,399
What?

96
00:08:53,399 --> 00:08:55,000
Nothing. Well,

97
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,159
So if I…

98
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,240
If I go, their performance

99
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:02,000
this year will improve.

100
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,159
That's for sure.

101
00:09:03,159 --> 00:09:04,480
That variety show now

102
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:06,639
is missing someone like you who is

103
00:09:06,639 --> 00:09:08,039
both refined and proper,

104
00:09:08,559 --> 00:09:10,559
authoritative and witty,

105
00:09:10,559 --> 00:09:12,480
with good image and great temperament.

106
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:13,519
To be honest with you,

107
00:09:13,519 --> 00:09:16,440
we've looked through the professors
from universities all over the country,

108
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,480
you're the most suitable one.

109
00:09:18,639 --> 00:09:19,639
The unparalleled choice, you know?

110
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,639
You're the only option.

111
00:09:21,639 --> 00:09:23,159
Chen, Chen, you, you…

112
00:09:23,159 --> 00:09:25,279
You, you, you're such a smooth talker.

113
00:09:25,279 --> 00:09:26,480
Let me give you a proper introduction.

114
00:09:27,039 --> 00:09:28,559
It's a talk show variety program,

115
00:09:29,159 --> 00:09:30,879
and they want your perspective as an economist

116
00:09:31,759 --> 00:09:34,200
to interpret modern young people's
emotional lives.

117
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:36,879
Okay.

118
00:09:36,879 --> 00:09:39,240
I'm very happy to hear
the praise you just gave me.

119
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,352
But,

120
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,159
as for the topic of relationships,

121
00:09:43,159 --> 00:09:45,840
to go exchange and discuss them, right?

122
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:49,519
I'm really not cut out for that.

123
00:09:50,639 --> 00:09:52,679
Professor Xu, young people these days

124
00:09:52,679 --> 00:09:54,120
don't like to be preached to.

125
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,519
But if there's someone like you

126
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,879
a professor of economics
with a fulfilled emotional life

127
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,320
to share views with them…

128
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,519
Fulfilled…

129
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:05,159
Many young people would love to have that.

130
00:10:05,679 --> 00:10:07,360
Young people these days
don't necessarily have to experience

131
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:09,080
dramatic ups and downs in relationships.

132
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,080
The quiet and ordinary is also real.

133
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:34,120
But even the quiet life has its troubles.

134
00:10:37,279 --> 00:10:38,799
As long as it's someone you care about deeply,

135
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,639
worries are just on the surface.

136
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:44,480
Deep inside, you're still happy.

137
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:54,440
<i>Most importantly, keep her in your heart</i>

138
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,399
<i>so that she can feel it.</i>

139
00:11:05,679 --> 00:11:06,816
Chen.

140
00:11:15,679 --> 00:11:19,559
Actually, Tang Wei talked to me

141
00:11:19,559 --> 00:11:20,919
about this variety show yesterday.

142
00:11:20,919 --> 00:11:22,799
I hadn't thought it through at the time.

143
00:11:27,639 --> 00:11:28,799
But now I have an answer.

144
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:30,784
Please.

145
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:33,312
I can do it.

146
00:11:35,879 --> 00:11:36,879
That's amazing.

147
00:11:37,919 --> 00:11:40,559
Professor Xu, I'd like to toast to you
on behalf of Ms. Wei.

148
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:45,399
Actually, Tang Wei also said
some things to me yesterday.

149
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,120
I think she is right.

150
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:54,720
Sometimes, I neglect the most
important people around me.

151
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:57,039
I take their kindness toward me

152
00:11:57,039 --> 00:11:58,360
for granted.

153
00:12:15,679 --> 00:12:18,919
Chen, have you read Eluard's poetry?

154
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,240
Eluard says

155
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:28,639
that men only grow old but never grow up.

156
00:12:31,639 --> 00:12:32,679
Tang Wei is right.

157
00:12:33,639 --> 00:12:35,440
After so many years, I am

158
00:12:38,399 --> 00:12:39,679
still a child.

159
00:12:40,799 --> 00:12:44,519
Professor Xu, please don't joke about me.

160
00:12:44,519 --> 00:12:46,639
I'm the child in front of you.

161
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,072
I'm the child.

162
00:12:54,039 --> 00:12:57,840
Come on, cheers to being a child.

163
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,912
A child.

164
00:13:06,399 --> 00:13:09,000
Let's ask the little bride. How do you feel?

165
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,519
I'm a little excited,

166
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:18,440
but also a bit scared.

167
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:23,120
How about you? Were you the same
before you got married?

168
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,720
We have all been through it.

169
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,039
It's not a big deal.

170
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:39,759
If it's wrong, it's wrong, right?

171
00:13:39,759 --> 00:13:43,200
If you feel that being together with someone

172
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,840
is not as good as being happy alone,

173
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:46,960
just split up.

174
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:48,480
Your mom is doing quite well now, isn't she?

175
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:52,608
Jiajia.

176
00:13:54,048 --> 00:13:55,840
Just listen to your own heart.

177
00:13:56,559 --> 00:13:58,159
There are so many choices in life.

178
00:13:58,159 --> 00:13:59,600
How can one think so far ahead?

179
00:14:00,399 --> 00:14:02,919
Being happy in the moment
is the most important thing.

180
00:14:02,919 --> 00:14:04,159
Just like what your mother said,

181
00:14:04,159 --> 00:14:06,440
even if you choose wrongly, it's not
the end of the world.

182
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:12,759
But there is one thing that I do hope to see.

183
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:15,320
You are Xu Jiajia.

184
00:14:16,279 --> 00:14:17,879
You should be yourself.

185
00:14:22,656 --> 00:14:23,840
- To Mom.
- Come on.

186
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:24,879
Come on.

187
00:14:24,879 --> 00:14:26,039
To Ms. Meng.

188
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:37,639
I have something I want to talk to you about.

189
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:41,559
Hao told me

190
00:14:42,399 --> 00:14:44,279
that if I didn't want to work
after getting married,

191
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,080
I could be a full-time housewife.

192
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,360
What do you say?

193
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:56,200
How much money does he give you a month, huh?

194
00:15:04,039 --> 00:15:08,720
The offer is quite generous.

195
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:09,856
No.

196
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:13,000
No matter how good the conditions are,

197
00:15:13,759 --> 00:15:16,080
you cannot be a housewife.

198
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,320
Once you become a housewife,

199
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:21,519
you'll lose your own space, you know?

200
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:25,480
At least, you must have a job of your own.

201
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:28,279
Aren't I the most typical case of failure?

202
00:15:28,279 --> 00:15:29,279
No, Meng.

203
00:15:29,279 --> 00:15:31,480
I don't think you are entirely correct.

204
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,240
Work is also very time-consuming and laborious.

205
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,559
I feel that I'm under a lot of pressure.

206
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:36,679
Think about it, after Jiajia gets married,

207
00:15:36,679 --> 00:15:39,159
she will have to manage her family, while
taking care of the children and her career.

208
00:15:39,159 --> 00:15:41,440
Won't that be exhausting?

209
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:42,528
So I think

210
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:46,080
career-oriented girls are not
suitable for marriage.

211
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:49,759
I still insist that being
a housewife is not an option.

212
00:15:49,759 --> 00:15:52,279
Jiajia, I insist that…

213
00:15:52,279 --> 00:15:53,759
It's really not what you think.

214
00:15:53,759 --> 00:15:55,279
If Jiajia became a housewife,

215
00:15:55,279 --> 00:15:57,440
her world would be confined.

216
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:59,320
She'll be entering a cage, you know?

217
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:00,352
How could it be?

218
00:16:00,352 --> 00:16:01,600
How is being a career woman better?

219
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:04,080
When working, she'll be busy every day.

220
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:05,600
Don't go out to work.

221
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:06,679
I see.

222
00:16:06,679 --> 00:16:09,320
You two are just jealous

223
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:11,440
of the path you didn't choose.

224
00:16:29,039 --> 00:16:30,120
It seems like it.

225
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:35,840
But Jiajia, let me tell you,

226
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:37,440
no matter which path you take,

227
00:16:38,639 --> 00:16:42,399
I will always be there
supporting you from behind.

228
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:48,000
So will Meng.

229
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:54,679
You have to be happy.

230
00:16:54,679 --> 00:16:56,879
I'm blissfully happy.

231
00:16:57,399 --> 00:16:58,879
Come on, let's have a drink.

232
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,880
Why are you always right?

233
00:18:11,559 --> 00:18:12,576
Meng.

234
00:18:15,279 --> 00:18:16,352
Meng?

235
00:18:18,759 --> 00:18:20,000
Meng, what's wrong? Meng.

236
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:24,759
Xu Jianming.

237
00:18:24,759 --> 00:18:26,640
Meng, what happened?

238
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:28,079
Let's break up.

239
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,112
What did you say?

240
00:18:30,839 --> 00:18:31,872
I said,

241
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:35,359
let's break up.

242
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,400
How… how many drinks did you have?

243
00:18:41,024 --> 00:18:42,079
You… Wait.

244
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:43,200
Are you sober right now?

245
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,839
I know what I'm saying.

246
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:50,440
It's been over a decade.

247
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:53,440
I've never been as sober as I am now.

248
00:18:54,799 --> 00:18:57,319
Xu Jianming, I love you.

249
00:19:01,839 --> 00:19:03,880
But in your eyes,

250
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:08,680
there's never been me.

251
00:19:11,759 --> 00:19:13,039
Never.

252
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:22,880
Meng, Meng.

253
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:24,359
I'm sorry.

254
00:19:24,359 --> 00:19:26,799
I didn't say all this

255
00:19:26,799 --> 00:19:29,079
to accuse you.

256
00:19:29,079 --> 00:19:31,039
- I know, I know.
- I understand.

257
00:19:31,039 --> 00:19:32,200
I didn't do well enough.

258
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,312
I know.

259
00:19:39,279 --> 00:19:40,799
You just don't love me anymore.

260
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:42,720
You just don't.

261
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:43,872
No.

262
00:19:53,248 --> 00:19:54,319
Meng, I…

263
00:19:54,319 --> 00:19:57,160
It's just that I don't want
to continue living like this.

264
00:19:59,119 --> 00:20:00,880
I don't want it to continue.

265
00:20:09,599 --> 00:20:10,960
Let's just end it here.

266
00:20:34,867 --> 00:20:42,240
<i>♫ Crossing clouds, surpassing regrets ♫</i>

267
00:20:43,168 --> 00:20:50,656
<i>♫ Causing me grief and pain ♫</i>

268
00:20:50,656 --> 00:20:54,464
<i>♫ Through the endless long night ♫</i>

269
00:20:54,464 --> 00:20:58,720
<i>♫ I sail through the darkness ♫</i>

270
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:03,200
<i>♫ Passing through many cities and villages ♫</i>

271
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:05,824
<i>♫ Passing through despair and hope ♫</i>

